    • serialize

      public static byte[] serialize(Tile tile)
      The serialize function takes a Tile object and returns a byte array. This is done by creating an ObjectOutputStream, which writes the tile to the ByteArrayOutputStream. The flush function is called on out, which flushes any buffered output bytes from this output stream and forces any buffered output bytes to be written out. The close function is called on bos, which closes the stream, releasing any system resources associated with it.
      Parameters:
      tile - Pass the tile object to the function
      Returns:
      A byte array
